Package game

Class Sewers

  • java.lang.Object
    • game.Sewers
  • public class Sewers
extends java.lang.Object
    An instance is a Sewers object through which a sewer diver can move.
    It's a grid of Tile objects with a weighted graph of all non-floor tiles. There is an entrance to the sewer system and a target location
    (which may also be the entrance).

    • Method Detail

      • digExploreSewer

        public static Sewers digExploreSewer​(int rows,
                                     int cols,
                                     java.util.Random rand)
        Return a new random sewer system of the given size where there are no coins,
        all edges have weight 1, and there is a ring a reasonable distance from the exit.
        Parameters:
        rows - The number of rows in this sewer system.
        cols - The number of columns in this sewer system.
        rand - A source of randomness to use for the sewer-system generation.

      • digGetOutSewer

        public static Sewers digGetOutSewer​(int rows,
                                    int cols,
                                    int currentRow,
                                    int currentCol,
                                    java.util.Random rand)
        Return a new random sewer system with random coins and edge weights.
        It is guaranteed that (currentRow, currentCol) will be an open floor cell.
        Parameters:
        rows - The number of rows in this sewer system.
        cols - The number of columns in this sewer system.
        currentRow - The row of the cell that must be open floor.
        currentCol - The column of the cell that must be open floor.
        rand - A source of randomness to use for the sewer-system generation.
